&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span&gt;Band 5 Musculoskeletal Physiotherapist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join our MSK Outpatient Physiotherapy team in the Solihull Community Service. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role will involve assessing and treating self referred and GP referred patients in our clinics, supervising students and contributing to service development initiatives.  We have robust mentoring structures in place to support you as a more junior member of the team.  Post graduate experience across core rotations is required –one rotation with appropriate experience must be in a musculoskeletal setting.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our service runs over 7 sites in the Solihull Borough so ability to transport yourself between sites is essential. We have strong links with our acute physiotherapy colleagues in the Trust and also work closely with Orthopaedic Triage. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a dynamic team that welcome change and new ideas.  We are always looking for new ways of working to enable us to continuously offer the highest quality service to our patients. To this end we have been working closely with our local leisure centres, which has facilitated the setting up of our ‘Breaking down barriers to exercise’ service. We have successfully implemented the spinal Pathfinder project for our low back pain patients. As part of our service we run an OSSUR Knee off loader brace clinic, Pilates classes, injection clinics and are also involved in a FCP pilot. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interview date: Thursday 26th November&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information regarding this post please contact:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Jenny Plagerson&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Clinical Team Leader for Solihull Community MSK Service&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;07554 439 149/0121 329 0152 (Working days Mon, Wed, Thurs)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
